# Payload 3 (backend)

- Define blocks with `import type { Block } from 'payload'`, **`slug` in camelCase** (matches `blockType` on stored documents and the frontend renderer).
- **Admin UI (de + en)**: **Every field** must use a bilingual label: `label: { de: '…', en: '…' }`. Do **not** use a plain string (`label: '…'`). The same applies wherever the admin shows copy: **block** `labels.singular` / `labels.plural`, **tab** and **group** labels, **array** `labels`, **select** / **radio** **option** `label` values, and **`admin.description`** / **`placeholder`** when you set them—always **`{ de, en }`** so editors can use Payload fully in German or English (`payload.config.ts` → `i18n.supportedLanguages: { de, en }`).
- Reuse **`@/fields`** helpers (`richTextField`, `link`, `buttonLink`, slug tabs, etc.) and the shared **Lexical** setup; avoid duplicating editor config unless the block truly needs a different feature set.
- **Register** new blocks on the relevant collection (e.g. `Pages` → `layout` → `blocks: [...]`).
- Use **`localized: true`** on fields that are translated; keep SEO/meta aligned with `@payloadcms/plugin-seo` fields where used.
- After schema changes: run **`pnpm --filter backend generate:types`** so `@payload-types` stays in sync for the frontend.

```ts
// Field label (required for every field)
{
  name: 'title',
  type: 'text',
  label: { de: 'Titel', en: 'Title' },
}

// Block labels (required)
labels: {
  singular: { de: '…', en: '…' },
  plural: { de: '…', en: '…' },
},
```
